<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= course.title %> - FinBuddy Learning</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/css/styles.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/css/learn.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/css/course.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css">
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('./partials/header') %>
    
    <main class="course-container" id="course-container" data-course-id="<%= course.id %>">
        <div class="course-header">
            <div class="course-detail-progress"></div>
            <div class="course-header-content">
                <h1><%= course.title %></h1>
                <div class="course-meta">
                    <span class="course-modules"><i class="fas fa-book"></i> <%= course.total_modules %> Modules</span>
                    <div id="course-progress" class="course-progress-indicator" 
                         data-progress="<%= progress.progress %>" 
                         data-total-modules="<%= course.total_modules %>">
                        <div class="progress-bar">
                            <div class="progress-fill" style="width: <%= progress.progress %>%"></div>
                        </div>
                        <span class="progress-text"><%= progress.progress %>% Complete</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="course-content">
            <div class="course-sidebar">
                <h3>Course Modules</h3>
                <ul class="module-list">
                    <li class="active">Introduction to <%= course.title %></li>
                    <li>Core Concepts</li>
                    <li>Practical Application</li>
                    <li>Advanced Strategies</li>
                    <li>Review & Assessment</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="course-resources">
                    <h3>Resources</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="#"><i class="fas fa-file-pdf"></i> Course PDF</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#"><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> Financial Calculator</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> Additional Reading</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="course-lesson">
                <h2>Introduction to <%= course.title %></h2>
                
                <p class="course-intro">
                    <%= course.description %>
                </p>
                
                <div class="lesson-section">
                    <h3>What You'll Learn</h3>
                    <ul class="learning-objectives">
                        <li>Understand the fundamentals of <%= course.title.toLowerCase() %></li>
                        <li>Develop practical skills for managing your finances</li>
                        <li>Apply key concepts to your own financial situation</li>
                        <li>Create a personalized plan for financial growth</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="lesson-section">
                    <h3>Key Concepts</h3>
                    <p>
                        Financial literacy is the foundation of sound money management. By understanding
                        the core principles of <%= course.title.toLowerCase() %>, you'll be equipped to make
                        better financial decisions.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="concept-cards">
                        <div class="concept-card">
                            <h4>Planning</h4>
                            <p>Creating a roadmap for your financial future</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="concept-card">
                            <h4>Implementation</h4>
                            <p>Putting strategies into action</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="concept-card">
                            <h4>Monitoring</h4>
                            <p>Tracking progress and making adjustments</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="lesson-section">
                    <h3>Real-World Application</h3>
                    <p>
                        Let's explore how these concepts apply to everyday financial situations:
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="example-scenario">
                        <h4>Scenario: Monthly Budget Planning</h4>
                        <p>
                            Sarah earns $4,000 per month and wants to create a budget that allows her to save
                            for a vacation while paying down her student loans. Using the 50/30/20 rule, she allocates:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>50% ($2,000)</strong> to necessities (rent, utilities, groceries)</li>
                            <li><strong>30% ($1,200)</strong> to wants (entertainment, dining out)</li>
                            <li><strong>20% ($800)</strong> to savings and debt repayment</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>
                            By following this approach, Sarah can systematically save for her vacation while reducing her debt.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="lesson-section">
                    <h3>Interactive Exercise</h3>
                    <p>
                        Take some time to apply these concepts to your own situation:
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="interactive-exercise">
                        <ol>
                            <li>List your monthly income sources</li>
                            <li>Categorize your expenses into needs and wants</li>
                            <li>Calculate what percentage you're currently saving</li>
                            <li>Identify one area where you could optimize your finances</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <div class="exercise-tip">
                            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
                            <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Start small with changes. Even minor adjustments can lead to significant improvements over time.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="lesson-navigation">
                    <button class="nav-button disabled">
                        <i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Previous
                    </button>
                    <button class="nav-button">
                        Next <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
    
    <%- include('./partials/footer') %>
    
    <script src="/public/js/auth.js"></script>
    <script src="/public/js/learn.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
